@Orman you may be disappointed in a regular-milk version, unless you figure out how much baking POWDER to substitute for the SODA called for! 

The reason you always see buttermilk (or other soured/fermented milks) along with baking soda is that soda is activated by acid. Without an acidic wet ingredient, the soda will just sit there, doing nothing.

If you use regular milk, add a spoonful of lemon juice or vinegar.

